[Name] Mailx
[Summary] mail user agent for Unix systems (previously known as nail)
[License] GNU General Public License (LGPL) V2
[Description] Mailx is derived from Berkeley Mail and is intended provide the functionality of the POSIX mailx command with additional support for MIME, IMAP, POP3, SMTP, and S/MIME. It provides enhanced features for interactive use, such as caching and disconnected operation for IMAP, message threading, scoring, and filtering. It is also usable as a mail batch language, both for sending and receiving mail.
[Homepage] http://heirloom.sourceforge.net/mailx.html
